race.description: In Memory Of Dot Robinson Handicap (Bm66)
race.comment: SUPAIRO (10) raced handy then let down well but found the winner far too good last start in a Class 2 over this course and distance. Has room to improve off that run and with a bit of luck from the sticky draw he can grab an elusive win. BEAU BANDIT (2) drove hard late and just arrived in time in a BM64 over 1200m at Newcastle recently. Defied the market that day but at just his fourth start was grossly underestimated. Can go on with the job in this easier assignment. SMART JAZZ (8) went back from a wide gate and struggled to get involved last start over 1450m here. Will be giving them a start but is one to watch for late in the piece. TURBULENT (9) made a little late ground when resuming at Coonamble last start. Can progress from that run over a bit more ground today. LEASE (3) is down in class and not out of contention fresh from a 30-day reset.
